At the link below you will find the Back to School Plan for Fisher Public School. A key part of this plan is our commitment to prioritize in-person learning whenever possible. While we continually communicate with Polk Co. Public Health to monitor the number of COVID cases in the area, based on current information, we are planning to start school on September 8 with full in-person learning.

As always, if you have any questions or concerns, please contact the school. We would be happy to clarify any information.

Thank you,
Fisher School Administrators

Graduation Update:
The Fisher High School Class of 2020 will have their graduation ceremony on Sunday, August 2nd at 2 pm. Based on the current limits for indoor gatherings, those attending the ceremony will be limited to the graduates, up to 10 invited guests per graduate, school board members and school faculty.

While we regret to say that the general public will not be able to attend the graduation ceremony this year, we do invite you to tune into the ceremony which will be live streamed. You can find the ceremony through the YouTube tab on the school's website or by following the link below.

Thank you on behalf of the Class of 2020 for the amazing community support.

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCxPCfzb_b20vELxEmQo5NGw/videos

post_text:
We know this is not the ideal way to spend your Senior Year of High School, so let's give our Seniors some love!

... Meet Alex!

Alex is the daughter of Elizabeth.

She celebrates her birthday on January 4.

Alex’s sibling is Ronnin.

Her favorite class Choir because she loves to sing. Her least favorite class in Animal Science.

Alex’s favorite food is olives and her favorite color is baby blue.

Mrs. Larson has been her favorite teacher. She was the best 3rd grade teacher.

Alex’s favorite memory from high school is playing Pictionary.

The year she was in 4th grade is her favorite elementary school memory.

In her spare time, you will find Alex relaxing with a good book as reading is her downtime activity of choice.

If Alex could change one thing about herself it would be her attitude.

Her advice to underclassmen is “Stay focused and keep your head up.”

After graduation, Alex plans to get a job and move out on her own.

Best of luck to you Alex!

post_text:
We know this is not the ideal way to spend your Senior Year of High School, so let's give our Seniors some love!

... Meet Cam!

Cam is the son of Tom and Becky.

He celebrates his birthday on December 14th.

Cam’s siblings are Claire and Trace.

Cam says that his favorite class would be Composition because he likes writing papers. His least favorite class is math because it gets too complicated.

Youth Service and getting to help out teachers this year is a favorite school activity for Cam.

His favorite food is chicken wings and his favorite color is orange.

Ms. Hensrud, the English teacher, is Cam’s favorite teacher because she has taught him lots of things to remember for college.

Being with friends is his favorite high school memory.

Gym class is Cam’s favorite elementary school memory.

In his spare time, he keeps himself busy with hunting and fishing

For employment, Cam works with a local carpenter.

His advice to underclassmen is “Good luck, you got a long road ahead.”

After graduation, Cam plans to continue with a career in carpentry.

Best of luck to you Cam!
